description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available as a Level 3 Apprentice Administration Assistant within ENT at The Princess Royal Hospital, Telford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide an administrative support service for the Medical/Support Secretaries, helping to prioritise work to ensure deadlines are met. &lt;br /&gt;Duties will include developing and maintaining effective communication skills to ensure a high quality service is provided when liaising with patients, GP’s and all other internal and external contacts. You will maintain good communication with health professionals and other groups within the Trust to ensure that patients receive appropriate and timely care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be willing to undertake and complete the Level 3 Business Administrator Apprenticeship within 18 months and should have a minimum of 4 GCSE’s or equivalent A* - D (9 – 4) (this must include Maths and English Language or equivalent) and must meet the minimum requirements of training provider for access to the apprenticeship programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A BTEC/Level 2 qualification in Business Administration and ECDL/CLAIT/GCSE or equivalent and a formal typing / word processing qualification is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Induction Training will be provided within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
